==English==
===Etymology===
From nineteenth-century dialect ''conker'', snail-shell; the game of [[conkers]] was originally played using snail-shells.

===Noun===
'''conker''' ({{plural}} '''conkers''')

#{{british}} A [[horse chestnut]] used in the game of [[conkers]].

